[34m│[0m ## General Payload Mutation & Bypass Framework                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Dimension 1: ENCODING TRANSFORMATIONS                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ENCODING LADDER (apply progressively):                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Raw          │ <script>         │ ../etc/passwd    │ ' OR 1=1                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m URL          │ %3Cscript%3E     │ ..%2Fetc%2Fpasswd│ %27%20OR                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Double-URL   │ %253Cscript%253E │ ..%252F...       │ %2527%20                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m HTML Entity  │ &#60;script&#62; │ &#46;&#46;/      │ &#39; OR                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Hex Entity   │ &#x3C;script&#x3E│ &#x2e;&#x2e;/    │ &#x27; OR               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Unicode      │ \u003Cscript\u003E│ \u002e\u002e/  │ \u0027 OR                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m UTF-8 Overlong│ %c0%bc (for <)  │ %c0%ae (for .)  │                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Base64       │ PHNjcmlwdD4=     │ Li4vZXRjL3Bhc3N3ZA== │                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **KEY INSIGHT:** Filters decode at one layer, execution happens at another.  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - If filter checks URL-decoded but backend double-decodes → double-encode    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - If filter checks raw but backend URL-decodes → URL-encode                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Dimension 2: CASE TRANSFORMATIONS                                        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m CASE MUTATION SPACE:                                                         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ────────────────────────────────────────────                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m lowercase    │ select, script, onclick                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m UPPERCASE    │ SELECT, SCRIPT, ONCLICK                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m MixedCase    │ SeLeCt, ScRiPt, OnClIcK                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Alternating  │ sElEcT, sCrIpT, oNcLiCk                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **WHY THIS WORKS:** Regex filters often case-sensitive, but parsers (HTML,   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m SQL) are case-insensitive.                                                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Dimension 3: WHITESPACE ALTERNATIVES                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m SPACE EQUIVALENTS (context-dependent):                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────         [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Context    │ Alternatives                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ───────────┼─────────────────────────────────────────────────────            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m HTML       │ / (tag separator), TAB (%09), NEWLINE (%0a, %0d)                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m            │ FORMFEED (%0c), NULL before space                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m SQL        │ /**/, %09, %0a, %0d, %0b, %a0 (nbsp), +, /*!*/                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Shell      │ ${IFS}, $IFS, {,}, <>, TAB, NEWLINE, \t, \n                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m URL        │ + (in query), %20, %09, no space (some parsers)                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m JS         │ /**/, /*!*/, template literals, \t, \n                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **PARSER INSIGHT:** Different parsers tokenize whitespace differently.       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - HTML sees <svg/onload=x> as valid                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - SQL sees SELECT/**/FROM as valid                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Dimension 4: QUOTE ALTERNATIVES                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
